    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Classes in Indo-European languages and certain other languages, into which nouns and pronouns are distinguished by different inflections which require other words to be in agreement with them. The types of classes typically are masculine, feminine, neuter, and common.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
